   210‚Üí        wrapper: bool = False,
   211‚Üí    ) -> _F | Callable[[_F], _F]:
   212‚Üí        """If passed a function, directly sets attributes on the function
   213‚Üí        which will make it discoverable to :meth:`PluginManager.register`.
   214‚Üí
   215‚Üí        If passed no function, returns a decorator which can be applied to a
   216‚Üí        function later using the attributes supplied.
   217‚Üí
   218‚Üí        :param optionalhook:
   219‚Üí            If ``True``, a missing matching hook specification will not result
   220‚Üí            in an error (by default it is an error if no matching spec is
   221‚Üí            found). See :ref:`optionalhook`.
   222‚Üí
   223‚Üí        :param tryfirst:
   224‚Üí            If ``True``, this hook implementation will run as early as possible
   225‚Üí            in the chain of N hook implementations for a specification. See
   226‚Üí            :ref:`callorder`.
   227‚Üí
   228‚Üí        :param trylast:
   229‚Üí            If ``True``, this hook implementation will run as late as possible
   230‚Üí            in the chain of N hook implementations for a specification. See
   231‚Üí            :ref:`callorder`.
   232‚Üí
   233‚Üí        :param wrapper:
   234‚Üí            If ``True`` ("new-style hook wrapper"), the hook implementation
   235‚Üí            needs to execute exactly one ``yield``. The code before the
   236‚Üí            ``yield`` is run early before any non-hook-wrapper function is run.
   237‚Üí            The code after the ``yield`` is run after all non-hook-wrapper
   238‚Üí            functions have run. The ``yield`` receives the result value of the
   239‚Üí            inner calls, or raises the exception of inner calls (including
   240‚Üí            earlier hook wrapper calls). The return value of the function
   241‚Üí            becomes the return value of the hook, and a raised exception becomes
   242‚Üí            the exception of the hook. See :ref:`hookwrapper`.
   243‚Üí
   244‚Üí        :param hookwrapper:
   245‚Üí            If ``True`` ("old-style hook wrapper"), the hook implementation
   246‚Üí            needs to execute exactly one ``yield``. The code before the
   247‚Üí            ``yield`` is run early before any non-hook-wrapper function is run.
   248‚Üí            The code after the ``yield`` is run after all non-hook-wrapper
   249‚Üí            function have run  The ``yield`` receives a :class:`Result` object
   250‚Üí            representing the exception or result outcome of the inner calls
   251‚Üí            (including earlier hook wrapper calls). This option is mutually
   252‚Üí            exclusive with ``wrapper``. See :ref:`old_style_hookwrapper`.
   253‚Üí
   254‚Üí        :param specname:
   255‚Üí            If provided, the given name will be used instead of the function
   256‚Üí            name when matching this hook implementation to a hook specification
   257‚Üí            during registration. See :ref:`specname`.
   258‚Üí
   259‚Üí        .. versionadded:: 1.2.0
   260‚Üí            The ``wrapper`` parameter.
   261‚Üí        """
   262‚Üí
   263‚Üí        def setattr_hookimpl_opts(func: _F) -> _F:
   264‚Üí            opts: HookimplOpts = {
   265‚Üí                "wrapper": wrapper,
   266‚Üí                "hookwrapper": hookwrapper,
   267‚Üí                "optionalhook": optionalhook,
   268‚Üí                "tryfirst": tryfirst,
   269‚Üí                "trylast": trylast,
   270‚Üí                "specname": specname,
   271‚Üí            }
   272‚Üí            setattr(func, self.project_name + "_impl", opts)
   273‚Üí            return func
   274‚Üí
   275‚Üí        if function is None:
   276‚Üí            return setattr_hookimpl_opts
   277‚Üí        else:
   278‚Üí            return setattr_hookimpl_opts(function)
